    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped as not-assessed at MRL 2. Discretization error factor achieves MRL 3 standard (GCI 2.1%). Validation against FDA interlaboratory benchmark demonstrates mean error of 8.3%, within the 15% acceptance criterion. UQ campaign across 200 parametric samples confirms robustness of the RH < 1 conclusion across the manufacturing tolerance space. The computational model is assessed as sufficiently credible to support the worst-case hemolysis operating condition identification decision for the Class II CPB device.",
